1. there is no way to use this tools without systemd. (asusctl and supergfxctl depending on it)
tbh. OpenRC and all the other standard-inits are nice, but not on modern desktop environments. state of the art is defacto systemd. (IMHO)

2. not mounting lvm (also when using luks/dm-crypt) is more a grub/initrd problem then systemd. (check your boot-configuration, for grub in example: /etc/default/grub)

Here are some things you should take a look into:
- gentoo systemd (https://wiki.gentoo.org/wiki/Systemd)
- gentoo lvm (https://wiki.gentoo.org/wiki/LVM)
- gentoo grub (https://wiki.gentoo.org/wiki/GRUB2)
- gentoo genkernel(https://wiki.gentoo.org/wiki/Genkernel) or dracut(https://wiki.gentoo.org/wiki/Dracut)
- zgentoo https://lab.retarded.farm/zappel/zGentoo
- emerge -a genfstab
- emerge -a ufed
